:orange_heart:*Please take a moment to review our Code of Conduct*:orange_heart:

We want the HubSpot Developer community to be inclusive and welcoming. By following our Code of Conduct, you can help ensure that's the case.

TL;DR:
• Be respectful
• Be inclusive (try not to say, "Hey guys, hey boys, hey [any specific group]")
• No self promotion, except for <#C0121KGC6RM|showcase> and <#CBNDYJJAZ|jobs> 
• No unsolicited DMs
Read the <https://developers.HubSpot.com/slack/code-of-conduct|whole thing here> - and thanks for being a part of the HubSpot Developer Community!

Want to report a violation? DM <@UQNEXHW14> or fill out the <https://form.asana.com/?k=p7aM0fpd3G4JGETDL_nYXg&d=8587152060687|anonymous form here>.
<@U04AQA0QM8E> maybe I'm missing something obvious here but... how do you "_completely disable the default “Form” module so that the forms script is never auto-bundled in your page resources_"?
You can add `@HubSpot/form` to the `hidden_modules` array in your theme.json file! If there aren’t any Form modules on a page, the v2.js script won’t be included in the script bundle.

Just found this one
<https://developers.HubSpot.com/docs/cms/building-blocks/themes/hide-modules-and-sections>
Thank you <@U04AQA0QM8E>! :hugging_face:
Oh, apologies — I forgot to include the link to that page in my message! Correct, that’s the functionality I was referring to. :)
No worries! I've simply searched it on my own because your words somewhat tickled my HS memory and there it is. So thanks again :sunglasses:
It's a year later and I'm still looking for this :thinking_face:

Hey, I have a js bug on my website and don’t know where it is coming from. A non displayed image is showing and its a gif from a G2 tracker code, I have already removed the google tag and disabled the tracking from G2 but it is still showing. I was told to check Javascript settings, as when I disable JS on chrome it disappears. How do I get to see Javascript settings on HS? This tag is not inside any .js file, how is it being generated?
